### HYMN XVI

#### A medical charm

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0601601">1</span></span>O Ābayu,
non-Ābayu, dire is thy juice, O Ābayu; we eat the  
   gruel made of thee.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0601602">2</span></span>Vihalha is
thy father's name, thy mother's is Madāvati.  
  Yea, verily thou art not he, thou who hast well protected life.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0601603">3</span></span>Go thou to
rest, Tauvilikā! This noisy cry hath sunk to rest.  
  Go hence, depart, Nirāla, thou! the tawny and the tawny-  
   eared.

